      • mapMappedInXYToLngLat

        public float[] mapMappedInXYToLngLat(float[] xyPoints)
        This function will consume an array of points in the x-y co-ordinate system used by various MappedIn objects and return an array of longitude-latitude co-ordinates that reference the current map's geo-location.

        Example:

        If this map object's top-left or north-west point referenced the north-pole at the Prime Meridian [lat = 90°, lng = 0°] and you passed in an array for a single point at [0px, 0px] (this referencing the top-left corner of the map), you will get back an array with a single point with [0°, 90°].
        Parameters:
        xyPoints - An array of points in the x-y co-ordinate system you want transformed
        Returns:
        An array of longitude-latitude points. This array will be all zeros if GPS is not enabled for this map.

      • mapMappedInXYToLngLat

        public void mapMappedInXYToLngLat(float[] lnglatsDest,
                         float[] xpPointsSrc)
        Parameters:
        lnglatsDest - The destination array that will be used to store the longitude-latitude co-ordinates
        xpPointsSrc - An array of points in the x-y co-ordinate system you want transformed
        See Also:

      • mapGeoMappedInLngLats

        public float[] mapGeoMappedInLngLats(float[] lnglats)
        This function will consume an array of longitude-latitude points that are within or near the geo-fence of this particular map and return an array of transformed longitude-latitude points that can then be used to draw, edit, modify points within the Google Maps renderer that is used by the MappedIn SDK.

        Example:

        If this map object's top-left or north-west point referenced the north-pole at the Prime Meridian [lat = 90°, lng = 0°] and you passed in an array with values [0°, 90°], you will get back a transformed value of [0°, 0°], which can then be used to draw markers or lines within the Google Map renderer on top of MappedIn maps.
        Parameters:
        lnglats - An array of points in the longitude-latitude co-ordinate system you want transformed
        Returns:
        An array of longitude-latitude points. This array will be all zeros if GPS is not enabled for this map.
